      "span_text": "This means that replacement of CS by CaS and/or partial replacement of any of both starches by either CF or AF hinders blended starch granules swelling during the process of gelatinization due to water competition, and composite starch polymer molecules (primarily amylose molecules) easily leach from the swollen granules [CITATION_1] , and thus, lower peak viscosity was reached.",
